The paper discusses the optimization of problems using evolutionary algorithms, which falls under the category of computational intelligence (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the optimization of linear functions with changing constraints, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper proposes a diversity mechanism to prevent the replacement of structurally good solutions, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper uses mathematical analysis to analyze the optimization time, which falls under the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
